The paper focuses on fast similarity search in large-scale information retrieval, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML). The use of neural networks and generative models also suggests a focus on deep learning (DL) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
